description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like the opportunity to work across different clinical areas, with the ability to choose the days and shifts you work? If so, this could be just the role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our nursing team in a new role of Staff Nurse – Flexible Working. The roles will work in various clinical areas in the hospital, being allocated an area to work on arrival for each shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role creates an opportunity to work within a range of acute wards and develop your clinical experience and knowledge across a broad spectrum of nursing care. Training and support will be provided relevant to your current experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Staff Nurse – Flexible Working will have permanent employment with East Cheshire NHS Trust, yet you will be able to self-roster and choose the days and shifts worked in advance, within your contracted hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applicants who are a band 5 qualified nurse with at least 12 months post registration experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like the role for you, please submit an application to join our nursing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week: full time and part time hours available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift patterns:shifts will be either early (7:00-15:00), late (13:00-20:00), long day (7:00-20:00) or night shifts (19:30-7:30)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For details about the role and ward/informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jill Marshall&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;jill.marshall7@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;01625 661251&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For queries regarding the application and or interview process, please contact the Recruitment Team either via email, ecn-tr.recruitment@nhs.net or telephone, 01625 656510&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We would like to inform you that if your application is successful, your interview will be held via SKYPE.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
